        <option value="http://www.hrc.org/hrc-story/available-internships"> - Available Internships</option>
          <option value="http://www.hrc.org/hrc-story/hrc-internship-application"> - Application</option>
          <option value="http://www.hrc.org/hrc-story/finding-housing"> - Finding Housing</option>
          <option value="http://www.hrc.org/hrc-story/securing-funding-for-your-internship"> - Secure Funding</option>
          <option value="http://www.hrc.org/hrc-story/internship-questions-answers"> - FAQs</option>
          <option value="http://www.hrc.org/hrc-story/celebrity-supporters">Celebrity Supporters</option>
        <option value="http://www.hrc.org/hrc-story/corporate-partners">Corporate Partners</option>
        <option value="http://www.hrc.org/hrc-story/contact-us">Contact Us</option>
        <option value="http://www.hrc.org/hrc-story/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</option>
        <option value="http://www.hrc.org/hrc-story/human-rights-campaign-copyright-complaint-notice">Copyright Complaint Notice</option>
        <option value="http://www.hrc.org/hrc-story/buy4equality-end-user-license-agreement">Buy4Equality End User License Agreement</option>
        <option value="http://www.hrc.org/hrc-story/community-discussion-guidelines">Community Discussion Guidelines</option>
        
</select>
</div>

		<p class="heading__copy">The Human Rights Campaign represents a force of more than 1.5 million members and supporters nationwide. As the largest national lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender civil rights organization, HRC envisions an America where LGBT people are ensured of their basic equal rights, and can be open, honest and safe at home, at work and in the community.</p>
		<div class="share-container share-container--explore">
			<p class="share-container__text">Share this</p>
